## Summary
Implemented all 6 units of vault trust boundary feature: inject modes with lazy/eager switching, recall/list/read CLI commands with ask-gating, access logging with rotation, `.claude/settings.json` integration, and documentation. TDD approach: 7 new test files, 142 tests passing, full lint clean, code review cleared (12 personas, no blockers). Branch stacked on session-manifest foundation; ready for PR pending stacking decision.

## Extraction Candidates
- **Lazy/eager injection pattern** (concept) — Design pattern for deferring trust-boundary check to init time while maintaining backward compatibility with eager opt-in
- **Access log minimization + rotation** (concept) — Structured audit trail that avoids PII/token leakage, rotates on size/age, compatible with read-raw hook gating
- **Ask-gated commands** (concept) — CLI read operations that require explicit consent via env var or config; unblocks future delegation to agents without consent
- **Trust boundary boundary enforcement** (concept) — Three-layer validation (Settings loader enforces policy, envelope envelope-write validates schema, access log traces every operation) prevents bypass
